        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 3 at 4:18PM EDT until July 3 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 417 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Bethel, or 11
miles west of Monticello, moving southeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and half dollar size hail.

SOURCE...Emergency management. This storm has a history of producing
widespread wind damage and large hail.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Monticello, Bethel, Damascus, Callicoon, Cochecton, Jeffersonville,
Stalker, Mongaup Valley, Maplewood, and Smallwood.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
